---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Colophon | Neku Akpotohwo" skyMode="receded">
  <div class="colophon">
    <header class="colophon__header">
      <h1>Colophon</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="colophon__section">
      <h2>About</h2>
      <p>
        I am Neku Akpotohwo. I study at Babcock University and help run GDG Babcock, where a thousand-something people learn to build together. I write, sometimes about philosophy, sometimes about engineering, mostly about the gap between the two.
      </p>
      <p>
        I like building things that feel alive. I like thinking about things that resist easy answers. I like being in rooms where people are making things they care about.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="colophon__section">
      <h2>How this site is built</h2>
      <p>
        Foothouse is a static site generated by <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro</a>. Content lives in <a href="https://supabase.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Supabase</a> (Postgres) and is fetched at build time. There is no client-side data fetching, no loading spinners. Just HTML.
      </p>
      <p>
        The sky follows your local time. It is a CSS gradient that paints before any JavaScript loads, then a canvas starfield fades in at night. The glass on the now-cards uses a computed displacement map (Snell's law, index of refraction 1.5, squircle dome) applied through an SVG filter. The sky is rendered twice: once as the real background, once as a counter-positioned copy behind each card, filtered to bend. This works in Safari, Firefox, and Chromium.
      </p>
      <p>
        The map uses <a href="https://maplibre.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MapLibre GL</a>, lazy-loaded only on the map page. Fonts are Fraunces (display) and DM Sans (body), self-hosted as woff2.
      </p>
      <p>
        When I edit content in Supabase Studio, a database webhook triggers a rebuild. The site redeploys in about 30 seconds. No CMS, no admin panel, just a table editor and a deploy hook.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="colophon__section">
      <h2>Find me</h2>
      <ul class="colophon__links">
        <li><a href="https://github.com/nekumartins" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://medium.com/@nekumartins" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Medium</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://twitter.com/nekumartins" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Twitter</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://linkedin.com/in/nekumartins" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .colophon {
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: calc(80px + var(--space-2xl)) var(--space-xl) var(--space-3xl);
  }

  .colophon__header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .colophon__header h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
  }

  .colophon__section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .colophon__section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--paper);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .colophon__section p {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .colophon__section a {
    color: var(--lamp);
    text-decoration-color: rgba(224, 164, 88, 0.3);
  }

  .colophon__section a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--lamp);
  }

  .colophon__links {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .colophon__links a {
    color: var(--paper);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 8px;
    transition: border-color 0.3s ease, color 0.3s ease;
  }

  .colophon__links a:hover {
    border-color: rgba(224, 164, 88, 0.3);
    color: var(--lamp);
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .colophon {
      padding-left: var(--space-md);
      padding-right: var(--space-md);
    }
  }
</style>
